In the Extended LoWPAN modality, the Backbone Link is used as a reference for address ownership and registration collision detection. Addresses that are not found in the Whiteboard are queried over the backbone using the ND operation in place for that type of link, typically ;
Edge Routers represent themselves and the LoWPAN Nodes that are proactively registered to them. An ND lookup over the backbone is not propagated over the LoWPANs,
but answered by the Edge Router that has the registration for the target, if any.
